                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The issue of the bilateral United States-Spanish talks on bases in Spain and the
                    possibility of future United States sponsorship of Spain in <gloss
                        target="#t_NAT1">NATO</gloss> were briefly discussed at the Fifth Meeting of
                    the Foreign Ministers of the United States, the United Kingdom, and France at
                    Washington on September 13, 1951. For the record of this meeting, see <ref
                        target="frus1951v03p1#pg_1279">volume III, Part 1, page 1279</ref>.</p>
            </div>
